    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-09-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="25" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <head>No. 329.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bassett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 10,
                            1875</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 239.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With the instruction No. 237, of the 2d
                        instant, a copy of the note of Mr. Preston<note n="*" xml:id="d25fn1">See
                            correspondence with the Haytian minister.</note> to this Department of
                        the 26th ultimo, which concludes with a proposition in regard to the
                        refugees under your protection, was transmitted. A copy of the reply to that
                        note is inclosed.<note n="*" xml:id="d25fn2">See correspondence with the
                            Haytian minister.</note> It contains a counter proposition upon the
                        subject. The reply will without doubt be communicated by Mr. Preston to his
                        government. If the proposition should be acceptable to the Haytian
                        government, you are authorized and directed to see that it is complied with
                        according to its terms.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                        Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
